r>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 5:45:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who should i side with in Velious?</span><hr size=1> For Velious armors wait until you are 50+ before worrying about those. You can't get thurgardin armors until 50 unless you buy MQ, and as for Kael or Skyshrine, Skyshrine stuff is better stat wise, but for either set you will have to be 55+ to get them since you must fight in different ToV wings for either set (Hall of Testing for SS West wing for Kael).<br><br>Its not worth waiting in Icewell to get royal velium armors. <p><center><image src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jayrj1/Fironasig.jpg><Br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133603>My Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 695<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 4:33:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who should i side with in Velious?</span><hr size=1> What is the deciding factor in which armor set/faction you choose?  Simply the stats?  or does Roleplaying enter into it?<br><br>Based simply on stats, I think you would want to choose Giant Faction.  Giant faction allows you to kill dwarves, who are pretty low in level, and dragons in Western Wastes and Skyshrine.  In Skyshrine Guardian and Sentry armor drops, which is pretty decent stuff.  And the Shining armor (the Kael Quest armor, as mentioned, 55+ stuff) has the best AC and pretty good stats.<br><br>Me and my wife made our decision about which factions to support based on something else though.  I just can't bring myself to kill dwarves (unless they're patently evil dwarves), since they can also be paladins.  Paladins = Good, so if your race can be paladins, then your race = good, to me.<br><br>One thing to consider though, Thurgadin is the only city on Velious where you can work tradeskills, so you should bear that in mind if you are interested in Tradeskills.  No real reason why you should start destroying your faction with the dwarves before you can actually DO any of the quests for the Giants, right? <p><div align="center"><font size="2">Aragir Lancot<BR><BR><font size="1">"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR>Cerivel tells you, 'Hehe grats on scaring off a level 56 giant that hits for 360'<BR><BR>Paladin of the 49th shield<BR><a href="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/">Exiles</a>, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 5:03:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who should i side with in Velious?</span><hr size=1> IMHO skyshrine armour is the best of all three velious quest armour sets. This armour has the best HP/resists and wis/mana. The armour class is a little lower than Kael armour but that becomes relatively unimportant once you are in full quest armour.<br><br>More importantly I would ask the question which armour am I most likely to obtain. From a difficulty perspective, thurgadin armour is the 'easiest' to get, followed by skyshrine armour and hardest is Kael armour. <br><br>For kael and skyshrine your guild needs to be able to fight in ToV. ToV does not have pickup raids so if you do not belong to a strong guild, then your chance of getting kael armour will be hard. A strong guild not in regards to quality of the guild but purely enough players of certain level and equipment. You need approximately 4-5 full groups for shyshrine and maybe 5-6 for kael armour fights. (This assumes everyone in the guild is just getting their feet wet in Tov and most are in kunark level loot)<br><br>If you are a casual player (you do not belong in a guild with 30+ active lvl 50+ and raid often 6 hour+)  then I would recomment siding with the dwarves and later when you reach 55 or so with skyshrine.<br><br>If you are a heavy trade and have access to good amounts of platinum, then MQ kael armour might be a choice you want to take. But it depends if people on your server sell MQ armour. <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 6:20:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who should i side with in Velious?</span><hr size=1> The largest deciding factor on which faction to choose is usually &quot;which faction is my guild on?&quot;. Once your guild picks a faction you will know which faction to work on. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>59 Knight of Brell<br> Master Brewer,